.TH "cpuidle_select" 9 "cpuidle_select" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpuidle_select \- ask the cpuidle framework to choose an idle state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cpuidle_select
.BI "(struct cpuidle_driver *drv "  ","
.BI "struct cpuidle_device *dev "  ","
.BI "bool *stop_tick "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drv" 12
the cpuidle driver
.IP "dev" 12
the cpuidle device
.IP "stop_tick" 12
indication on whether or not to stop the tick
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the index of the idle state.  The return value must not be negative.

The memory location pointed to by \fIstop_tick\fP is expected to be written the
'false' boolean value if the scheduler tick should not be stopped before
entering the returned state.
